	Standard markup language for creating web pages.

What is HTML?
	1. HTML stands for Hyper Text Markup Language
	2. Standard language for creating web pages
	3. Defines the structure of the webpages
	4. Contains series of HTML elements
	5. Elements tell web browser how to display the content
	6. Elements label pieces of content as this is header, this is paragraph, this is link

Simple HMTL Document

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
		<title>My First Web Page</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1>My Life</h1>
		<p>Everyone has life thatâ€™s why we talk about life. How we live in our life is different</p>
	</body>
</html>

More Details
It has 2 parts
	1. Declaration
	2. Elements

Declaration:
<!DOCTYPE html> : declaration that defines this is HTML5 document

Elements:
<html>,<head>,<title>,<body>,<h1>,<p>

<html>: root element of a HTML page
<head>: contains meta data information of HTML page
<title>: defines title of the HTML Page(shown in browser title bar or in pages tab)
<body>: defines document body, its a container of all visible contents such as heading, paragraphs, images, hyperlinks, tables, list, etc.
<h1>: defines a large heading
<p>: defines a paragraph 
	
What is HTML element?
HTML element defined by - start tag, content and end tag.
<start_tag>content></tag_end>
Example:
<h1>My first heading</h1>
<p>My first paraghaph</p>
<br>

some elemnts do not have content and end tag they are called empty elements like <br>.

Web Browsers
Web browsers like chrome, edge, safari, internet explorer, firefox reads HTML document and based on the element defined displays the content.

HTML Page Structure
<html>
	<head>
		<title> My WebPage Title</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1>Heading</h1>
		<p>Paragraph 1</p>
		<p>Paragraph 2</p>
	</body>
</html>

The content inside body section is displayed in the web broswer
The content inside <title> is displayed on browser title bar or tab page.


HTML History

Many versions of HTML are available since the rise of World Wide Web.

Year	Version
1989	Tim Berners-Lee invented www
1991	Tim Berners-Lee invented HTML
1993	Dave Raggett drafted HTML+
1995	HTML Working Group defined HTML 2.0
1997	W3C Recommendation: HTML 3.2
1999	W3C Recommendation: HTML 4.01
2000	W3C Recommendation: XHTML 1.0
2008	WHATWG HTML5 First Public Draft
2012	WHATWG HTML5 Living Standard
2014	W3C Recommendation: HTML5
2016	W3C Candidate Recommendation: HTML 5.1
2017	W3C Recommendation: HTML5.1 2nd Edition
2017	W3C Recommendation: HTML5.2


